                         @{b}Spis v1.0 by Inikep/Genetic@{ub}

@{i}Program  Spis  is created to make list of files and dirs, which are on hard@{ui}
@{i}disc, floppy disc or any device of AmigaDos.  This is something like system@{ui}
@{i}dir command, but Spis reads all subdirs, have GUI, recognises file formats,@{ui}
@{i}can decrunching FILE_ID.DIZ from archives and much more...@{ui}

       @{"   Requirements   " LINK WYMAGANI}    What is necessary to run Spis.
       @{"      Autors      " LINK AUTORSPI}    Copyright and addresses.
       @{"    Instruction   " LINK OPISPROG}    About functions of program.

@ENDNODE





@NODE WYMAGANI "Spis - requirements"
@{B}@{U}Requirements@{UB}@{UU}

Hardware:
  Program Spis needs Kickstart 1.3 or higher and about 300KB free memory.

Software:
  reqtools.library
  powerpacker.library  -  in  case   of  depacking   data  packed  with  PP
  xpkmaster.library  - in  case   of  depacking   data   packed   with  XPK
  crm.library  - in  case  of  depacking   data  packed   with  Crunchmania
  LHA in C: directory - if you  need  to depack  FILE_ID.DIZ  from archives
                                                            packed with LHA
  LZX in C: directory - if you  need  to depack  FILE_ID.DIZ  from archives
                                                            packed with LZX


Compatibility:
  This program  shall  work  on  all  computers,  was  tested  on different
  configurations:
 
  A500/000/7MHz,   Kickstart 1.3, 0.5MB chip+0.5MB fast
  A1200/020/14MHz, Kickstart 3.0, 2MB chip
  A1200/020/14MHz, Kickstart 3.0, 2MB chip+4MB fast
  A1200/030/50Mhz, Kickstart 3.0, 2MB chip+4MB fast
  A1200/040/25MHz, Kickstart 3.0, 2MB chip+8MB fast
  Pentium/133Mhz,  Kickstart 2.0, 2MB chip
  Pentium/133Mhz,  Kickstart 3.1, 2MB chip+8MB fast

  This Pentium it is not a joke, program was tested on PC with emulator of
  Amiga UAE 0.6.4.

@ENDNODE




