@NODE WYBOR "Spis - buttons"
Dir name - you can choose directory or device from to make file-list

Save as - you can choose name and place, where to do file-list
@ENDNODE





@NODE MENU "Spis - buttons2"
Start - start of making file-list

Info - informations about main autor of program, about number of recognising
       file formats and about date of compiling (creating Spis)

Quit  -  you can leave program, iconify program or you can back to menu



Save config  - saving configuration to file S:Spis.config (lub if S: don't
        exists to file SYS:Spis.config)
@ENDNODE





@NODE JEZYK "Spis - languages"
English - all buttons and informations in english

Polish - all buttons and informations in polish

AmigaPL - polish language with polish letters in standard AmigaPL
@ENDNODE





@NODE OPCJE "Spis - options"
@{B}@{U}What doing option on (when appears "V")@{UB}@{UU}

Decrunching files  -   this  option  can  depacking  files  packed  with  XPK
                  PowerPacker,  Crunchmania  and  StoneCracker  and  you  can
                  to know about  file format of  packed file,  of course this
                  option works only with "Writing file format"

Writing file format - recognising file  format and  including  file format to
                  file-list,  if  you  want  to  know  about  file  format of
                  packed file you can use "Decrunching files" option

Writing file comment  -  if file  have comment,  comment will  be included in
                  file-list

Including FILE_ID.DIZ  -  including FILE_ID.DIZ (if exist) from archives LHA,
                  LZX, DMS and text-files

Filtering *.info  -  filtering all files with extension "info" (mainly icons)
@ENDNODE
